%20to%20find%20footing%20in%20a%20traditionally%20rarefied%20funding%20ecosystem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20founders%20%E2%80%94%20Yoav%20Anaki%2C%20Yuval%20Efrat%2C%20Lisa%20Yan%2C%20Insoo%20Chang%2C%20Lindsay%20Atkeson%2C%20Madison%20McIlwain%2C%20and%20Rob%20Muldowney%20%E2%80%94%20began%20discussions%20during%20the%202023%20to%202024%20school%20year%2C%20and%20started%20fundraising%20in%20earnest%20in%20September.%20They're%20closing%20the%20fund%20this%20month%20and%20will%20begin%20deploying%20it%20in%20April%20over%20a%20five-year%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20recruited%20a%20cadre%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frising-stars-of-the-venture-capital-industry-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh-profile%20venture%20capitalists%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20advisors%20including%20Alex%20Kayyal%2C%20partner%20at%20Lightspeed%20Venture%20Partners%2C%20Bryan%20Kim%20partner%20at%20Andreessen%20Horowitz%2C%20Sara%20Choi%2C%20partner%20at%20Wing%20Venture%20Capital%2C%20and%20Sanjay%20Rao%2C%20managing%20partner%20at%20Tau%20Ventures.%20Several%20of%20its%20more%20than%2010%20advisors%20are%20alumni%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-dropped-out-business-entrepreneur-dub-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHBS%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20no%20surprise%20that%20Harvard%20Business%20School%20people%20are%20doing%20business%20together%2C%20right%3F%20That%20is%20the%20genesis%20of%20the%20school%2C%26quot%3B%20McIlwain%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Twenty25's%20%26quot%3Bthesis%20is%20if%20you%20just%20backed%20an%20index%20of%20HBS%20graduates%20in%20your%20class%20you%20would%20outperform%20the%20S%26amp%3BP.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarvard%20MBA%20graduates%20have%20raised%20close%20to%20%2480%20billion%20in%20venture%20capital%20funding%20in%20the%20past%20decade%2C%20more%20than%20any%20other%20business%20school%2C%20according%20to%20PitchBook.%20The%20school's%20top-funded%20companies%20include%20battery%20maker%20Northvolt%2C%20used%20car%20marketplace%20Kavak%2C%20and%20cloud%20security%20startup%20Lacework.%20It%20came%20in%20second%20after%20Stanford%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business%20for%20the%20greatest%20number%20of%20unicorn%20founders%2C%20producing%20about%204.2%20per%201%2C000%20graduates%2C%20according%20to%20a%20LinkedIn%20post%20from%20Stanford%20professor%20Ilya%20Strebulaev.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwenty25%20will%20invest%20in%20startups%20raising%20%24500%2C000%20or%20more%20in%20rounds%20led%20by%20institutional%20investors%20and%20select%20venture%20capital%20firms.%20The%20average%20investment%20check%20size%20will%20be%20between%20%2410%2C000%20and%20%2450%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20goal%20is%20to%20give%20more%20HBS%20students%20a%20chance%20to%20tap%20into%20their%20exclusive%20network%20before%20they%20embark%20on%20their%20careers%20and%20build%20wealth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20wanted%20to%20lower%20the%20barrier%20to%20entry%20and%20give%20more%20of%20our%20classmates%20the%20chance%20to%20participate%20in%20venture%20investing%2C%26quot%3B%20McIlwain%20said.%20%26quot%3BGenerational%20wealth%20creation%20begins%20with%20access.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fund%20takes%20student%20checks%20as%20low%20as%20%243%2C000%20and%20caps%20them%20at%20%24100%2C000%2C%20or%2010%25%20of%20the%20fund.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222113f5c0-7933-49ed-a319-b75537175b26%5C%22%3EStudents%20want%20to%20bet%20on%20each%20other%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EHarvard's%20fund%20is%20inspired%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstanford-business-students-formed-a-club-to-invest-in-classmates-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStanford%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20venture%20capital%20fund%20launched%20by%20Stanford%20Graduate%20School%20of%20Business%20students%20in%202020%20to%20invest%20in%20their%20classmates'%20startups.%20The%20fund%20garnered%20backing%20from%20nearly%20half%20of%20the%202020%20class%2C%20raising%20over%20%241.5%20million%2C%20and%20had%20a%20minimum%20of%20%243%2C000%20for%20contributions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%202020%20interview%20with%20TechCrunch%2C%20Stanford%202020%20founder%20Steph%20Mui%20said%20the%20fund%20was%20born%20from%20the%20inaccessibility%20of%20angel%20investing%20%E2%80%94%20through%20which%20high%20net-worth%20individuals%20put%20capital%20into%20early-stage%20ventures%3A%20%26quot%3BOnly%20accredited%20people%20can%20do%20it%2C%20it%20feels%20very%20elite%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20started%20thinking%20more%20about%20if%20we%20can%20actually%20make%20this%20something%20that%20the%20whole%20class%20could%20participate%20in%2C%20or%20at%20least%20make%20it%20more%20accessible%20to%20more%20than%20just%20like%20these%20small%20pockets%20of%20people%20that%20do%20it%20behind%20closed%20doors%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20later%20told%20the%20outlet%20that%20the%20majority%20of%20people%20who%20contributed%20to%20Stanford%202020%20were%20first-time%20check%20writers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPIN%2C%20which%20stands%20for%20Power%20in%20Numbers%2C%20is%20a%20platform%20that%20Mui%20spun%20out%20of%20Stanford%202020.%20It%20handles%20all%20of%20the%20administrative%2C%20legal%2C%20and%20tax%20work%20for%20investment%20clubs.%20Twenty25%20is%20utilizing%20it%20because%20it%20makes%20it%20easier%20to%20handle%20smaller-scale%20checks%20than%20a%20standard%20platform%20for%20syndicates.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20student-backed%20funds%20with%20similar%20structures%20have%20sprung%20up%20at%20other%20business%20schools.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20at%20University%20of%20California%20Berkeley's%20Haas%20School%20of%20Business%20launched%20Courtyard%20Ventures%20in%202021%2C%20which%20has%20since%20deployed%20over%20%243%20million%20across%20multiple%20funds%2C%20investing%20about%20%2450%2C000%20to%20%24100%2C000%20per%20startup%2C%20according%20to%20its%20website.%20Its%20general%20partners%20also%20invest%20about%20half%20of%20their%20performance%20fees%20into%20campus%20groups%20supporting%20startups.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20two%20members%20of%20Wharton's%20class%20of%202026%20launched%20Center%20City%20Ventures.%20The%20fund%20collects%20contributions%20from%20students%20in%20the%20class%20of%202026%20starting%20at%20%243%2C000%2C%20and%20will%20invest%20the%20money%20into%20startups%20founded%20across%20the%20university%2C%20according%20to%20its%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20past%20few%20years%20have%20been%20tough%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmba-graduates-cant-find-jobs-white-collar-hiring-slowdown-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMBA%20graduates%3C%2Fa%3E%20including%20ones%20from%20the%20most%20elite%20institutions.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhiring-slump-professional-white-collar-jobs-recession-high-salary-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhite-collar%20hiring%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20taken%20a%20hit%20and%20cut%20the%20amount%20that%20companies%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20post-MBA%20hires.%20The%20share%20of%20graduates%20from%20top%20schools%20like%20Harvard%2C%20Stanford%2C%20and%20Wharton%20with%20jobs%20three%20months%20after%20graduation%20has%20declined%20since%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20class%20funds%20at%20these%20schools%20make%20the%20case%20that%20students%20see%20real%20value%20in%20their%20network.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20fund%20isn't%20just%20about%20startups%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20about%20inclusion%2C%20ownership%2C%20and%20community.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fharvard-business-school-students-launch-class-backed-vc-fund-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743453179000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.