s%3A%2F%2Fabout.usps.com%2Fnewsroom%2Fnational-releases%2F2024%2F1114-usps-reports-fiscal-year-2024-results.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etotal%20loss%20for%20the%20fiscal%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%20ending%20in%20September%20was%20%249.5%20billion%2C%20a%20%243%20billion%20increase%20from%20its%20loss%20the%20previous%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20agency's%20financial%20woes%20led%20then-Postmaster%20General%20Louis%20DeJoy%20%E2%80%94%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.usps.com%2Fnewsroom%2Fnational-releases%2F2025%2F0324-usps-pmg-ceo-leadership-transition.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estepped%20down%20from%20his%20role%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20week%20%E2%80%94%20in%20mid-March%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fabout.usps.com%2Fwho%2Fgovernment-relations%2Fassets%2Fpmg-letter-to-congress-03172025.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommit%20to%20working%20with%20DOGE%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20make%20the%20agency%20more%20efficient%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foversightdemocrats.house.gov%2Fsites%2Fevo-subsites%2Fdemocrats-oversight.house.gov%2Ffiles%2Fevo-media-document%2Fpmg-dejoy-to-congressional.leaders_3.13.2025.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecutting%2010%2C000%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20eliminating%20billions%20of%20dollars%20from%20the%20budget.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c0cbb76a-1a34-464f-9314-be65e428018b%5C%22%3EHigher%20prices%2C%20reduced%20service%20to%20some%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20USPS%20were%20privatized%2C%20it's%20not%20clear%20if%20existing%20laws%20regulating%20the%20agency%2C%20like%20mandating%20six%20days%20of%20service%20and%20universal%20delivery%2C%20would%20remain%20in%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20a%20private%20company%20were%20to%20take%20over%20USPS%20operations%20and%20those%20laws%20were%20thrown%20out%20the%20window%2C%20it%20would%20likely%20drive%20up%20prices%2C%20reduce%20delivery%20speed%20and%20frequency%2C%20eliminate%20service%20to%20all%20addresses%2C%20and%20close%20some%20of%20the%20over%2030%2C000%20USPS%20offices%20around%20the%20country%2C%20said%20Michael%20Plunkett%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20Association%20for%20Postal%20Commerce%2C%20which%20represents%20mailing%20and%20shipping%20industry%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20communities%20would%20%26quot%3Balmost%20certainly%26quot%3B%20feel%20more%20pain%20than%20others%2C%20Plunkett%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20are%20rural%20communities%20that%20would%20probably%20suffer%20if%20the%20postal%20service%20were%20changed%20in%20any%20significant%20way%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20short%20run%2C%26quot%3B%20Plunkett%20said.%20And%20that's%20because%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20no%20other%20operator%20in%20many%20small%20and%20remote%20towns%20in%20the%20United%20States.%20That's%20why%20the%20postal%20service%20does%20last-mile%20delivery%20for%20other%20companies%20in%20those%20places.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Rourke%20said%20that%20even%20though%20the%20agency%20isn't%20as%20popular%20as%20it%20once%20was%2C%20it%20should%20still%20be%20treated%20as%20an%20essential%20public%20service.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20concerns%20me%20the%20most%20is%20that%20we%20become%20two%20nations%3A%20the%20haves%20and%20have%20nots%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20the%20gap%20between%20the%20two%20widens%20and%20the%20services%20available%20are%20no%20longer%20available%20to%20those%20who%20need%20them%20just%20as%20much%20as%20the%20others.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2245f6044e-c648-4095-bc21-080f555cef04%5C%22%3ESignificant%20reforms%20would%20also%20hurt%20nonprofits%20and%20businesses%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20nonprofit%20world%20still%20relies%20heavily%20on%20the%20mail%20for%20its%20fundraising%20efforts%2C%20said%20Robert%20Tigner%2C%20regulatory%20counsel%20at%20The%20Nonprofit%20Alliance%2C%20an%20association%20that%20represents%20and%20advocates%20for%20nonprofits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20USPS%20were%20privatized%20and%20discounted%20nonprofit%20mailing%20rates%20taken%20away%2C%20there%20would%20be%20a%20devastating%20impact%20on%20organizations%2C%20Tigner%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20%E2%80%94%20even%20a%20big%20organization%20doesn't%20have%20an%20extra%20six%20or%20seven%20million%20lying%20around%20in%20order%20to%20continue%20what%20it's%20doing%20today%2C%26quot%3B%20Tigner%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20would%20cripple%20the%20current%20environment%20of%20raising%20money%20through%20the%20mail.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20not%20just%20nonprofits%20who%20would%20take%20a%20hit%20from%20higher%20prices.%20Any%20business%20that%20relies%20on%20the%20mail%20for%20advertising%20would%20suffer%20too%2C%20Plunkett%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAny%20major%20change%20in%20how%20the%20postal%20service%20operates%20would%20be%20sufficiently%20disruptive%20that%20it%20would%20cause%20some%20companies%20and%20nonprofits%20to%20go%20out%20of%20business%2C%26quot%3B%20Plunkett%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a72ac111-10d3-4622-9182-164967e9af27%5C%22%3EStill%2C%20some%20say%20privatizing%20has%20its%20benefits%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20would%20not%20be%20the%20first%20to%20privatize%20or%20reduce%20its%20mail%20service%20%E2%80%94%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgeorge-osborne-plans-to-raise-31-billion-through-public-sector-sell-offs-in-2015-2015-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20UK%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Germany%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftile.loc.gov%2Fstorage-services%2Fservice%2Fll%2Fllglrd%2F2021687439%2F2021687439.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Netherlands%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20privatized%20their%20post%20offices%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-wants-privatize-usps-post-denmark-stops-letter-delivery-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDenmark's%20state-run%20postal%20service%3C%2Fa%3E%20recently%20announced%20it%20w