form%20X.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EInteresting%20that%20Yunus%20is%20making%20a%20public%20appeal%20to%20the%20Chinese%20on%20the%20basis%20that%207%20states%20in%20India%20are%20land-locked.%20China%20is%20welcome%20to%20invest%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20but%20what%20exactly%20is%20the%20significance%20of%207%20Indian%20states%20being%20landlocked%3F%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FJHQAdIzI9s%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FJHQAdIzI9s%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Sanjeev%20Sanyal%20(%40sanjeevsanyal)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fsanjeevsanyal%2Fstatus%2F1906602602059489289%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EMarch%2031%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Sanyal%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BInteresting%20that%20Yunus%20is%20making%20a%20public%20appeal%20to%20the%20Chinese%20on%20the%20basis%20that%207%20states%20in%20India%20are%20land-locked.%20China%20is%20welcome%20to%20invest%20in%20Bangladesh%2C%20but%20what%20exactly%20is%20the%20significance%20of%207%20Indian%20states%20being%20landlocked%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECHINA'S%20PLANS%20IN%20BANGLADESH%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Yunus%2C%20who%20held%20detailed%20discussions%20with%20China's%20Xi%20Jinping%20during%20his%20visit%2C%20thanked%20Beijing%20for%20agreeing%20to%20his%20appeal%20for%20China%20to%20enhance%20maritime%20cooperation%20with%20Dhaka.%20The%20two%20nations%20signed%20an%20agreement%20for%20Chinese%20companies%20to%20%26quot%3Bparticipate%20in%20modernisation%20and%20expansion%20of%20Bangladesh's%20Mongla%20Port%26quot%3B.%20The%20two%20sides%20also%20agreed%20to%20collaborate%20to%20develop%20and%20expand%20the%20Chinese%20Economic%20and%20Industrial%20Zone%20in%20Chattogram%2C%26quot%3B%20Bangladesh's%20foreign%20ministry%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20a%20report%20in%20Bangladesh's%20state-run%20news%20agency%20Bangladesh%20Sangbad%20Sangstha%2C%20China%20has%20agreed%20to%20spending%20%24400%20million%20to%20modernize%20and%20expand%20Mongla%20Port%2C%20and%20has%20allocated%20%23350%20million%20for%20expanding%20the%20China%20Economic%20and%20Industrial%20Zone.%20An%20additional%20%24150%20million%20has%20been%20reserved%20for%20providing%20technical%20assistance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20this%2C%20My%20Yunus%20pleaded%20with%20Beijing%20to%20provide%20a%2050-year%20assistance%20to%20Bangladesh%20over%20river%20water%20management.%20%26quot%3BChina%20is%20the%20master%20of%20water%20management%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Yunus%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20come%20to%20learn%20from%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20Bangladesh's%20state-run%20media%20agency%20quoted%20him%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBangladesh%20has%20asked%20China%20to%20help%20it%20manage%20its%20Teesta%20river%2C%20which%20it%20jointly%20shared%20with%20India.%20India%20being%20upstream%2C%20Sheikh%20Hasina's%20government%20had%20sought%20direct%20cooperation%20with%20New%20Delhi%20on%20the%20matter%2C%20but%20the%20Yunus%20government%20wants%20Beijing's%20intervention%20in%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20asked%20for%20help%20manage%20its%20overall%20river%20waters.%20%26quot%3BBangladesh's%20problem%20lies%20not%20just%20with%20one%20river%2C%20but%20its%20overall%20river%20system%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Yunus%20reportedly%20told%20Xi%20Jinping.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20countries%20also%20signed%20an%20agreement%20on%20the%20Exchange%20of%20Hydrological%20Information%20for%20the%20Yarlung%20Zangbo-Jamuna%20River%2C%20which%20flows%20from%20Tibet%20to%20India%2C%20before%20merging%20with%20the%20Ganga%20river%20and%20entering%20Bangladesh.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743435480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Ftns37fdc_xi-jinping-muhammad-yunus-xi-jinping-ians_625x300_31_March_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https