s%20case%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHindustan%20Aeronautics%20Limited%2C%20or%20HAL%2C%20has%20not%20yet%20responded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20row%20broke%20after%20the%20%3Cem%3ENew%20York%20Times%3C%2Fem%3E%20published%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2025%2F03%2F28%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Freform-uk-donor-farage-technology-russia-sanctions-india.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20-%20'Major%20Donor%20to%20Reform%20U.K.%20Party%20Sold%20Parts%20Used%20In%20Weapons%20to%20Russian%20Supplier'%20-%20on%20March%2028.%20The%20Reform%20UK%20party%20is%20led%20by%20Nigel%20Farage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20British%20aerospace%20manufacturer%20HR%20Smith%20Group%20had%20shipped%20-%20via%20HAL%20-%20nearly%20%242%20million%20in%20transmitters%2C%20cockpit%20equipment%2C%20and%20other%20sensitive%20tech%2C%20which%20are%20among%20those%20the%20British%20and%20Americans%20have%20said%20cannot%20be%20sold%20to%20Russia%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20claimed%20that%20%26quot%3Bin%20some%20instances%20the%20Indian%20company%20(i.e.%2C%20HAL)%20received%20equipment%20from%20HR%20Smith%20and%2C%20within%20days%2C%20sent%20parts%20to%20Russia%20with%20the%20same%20identifying%20product%20codes%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20essence%2C%20NYT%20-%20which%20said%20it%20had%20reviewed%20shipping%20records%20-%20said%20HR%20Smith%20made%20118%20shipments%20of%20restricted%20tech%20to%20HAL%20over%202023%20and%202024.%20These%20were%20worth%20%242%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHAL%2C%20in%20that%20period%2C%20reportedly%20made%2013%20shipments%20of%20the%20same%20parts%20to%20Rosoboroneexport%2C%20a%20Russian%20arms%20agency%20blacklisted%20by%20the%20United%20States%20and%20the%20United%20Kingdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20shipments%20were%20worth%20over%20%2414%20million.%20Rosoboroneexport%20is%20reportedly%20one%20of%20HAL's%20biggest%20trading%20partners.%