ant%20message.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20immoral%20and%20tyrannical%20approach%20will%20undoubtedly%20be%20overturned%20by%20the%20will%20and%20resilience%20of%20our%20people.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImamoglu%20was%20taken%20to%20a%20high-security%20police%20station%20in%20Istanbul%20and%20was%20later%20shifted%20to%20Turkey's%20notorious%20Silivri%20prison%20on%20the%20edge%20of%20the%20city%20after%20his%20formal%20arrest%20on%20what%20are%20seen%20as%20trumped-up%20charges%20of%20corruption%20and%20terrorism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20arrest%20triggered%20a%20wave%20of%20mass%20protests%20across%20Turkey%2C%20posing%20the%20biggest%20threat%20to%20President%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdogan's%2022-year%20rule.%20Turkey%20hasn't%20seen%20such%20large%20protests%20since%20the%202013%20Gezi%20uprising%20in%20Istanbul%2C%20which%20resulted%20in%20a%20brutal%20crackdown%20by%20his%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20Is%20Erdogan%20Afraid%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImamoglu%20was%20taken%20into%20custody%20days%20before%20he%20was%20expected%20to%20be%20chosen%20by%20his%20Republican%20People's%20Party%20(CHP)%20as%20the%202028%20presidential%20nominee.%20Long%20seen%20as%20the%20main%20political%20rival%20to%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdogan%2C%20Imamoglu%20had%20been%20leading%20in%20opinion%20polls%20even%20before%20his%20detention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20eve%20of%20his%20arrest%2C%20Istanbul%20University%20declared%20Imamoglu's%20degree%20null%2C%20making%20him%20ineligible%20to%20run%20for%20the%20presidency.%20Higher%20education%20is%20a%20requirement%20in%20Turkey%20for%20presidential%20candidates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20presidential%20elections%20are%20not%20due%20in%20the%20country%20until%202028%2C%20and%20Erdogan%20is%20not%20eligible%20to%20run%20for%20a%20third%20term.%20So%2C%20why%20should%20he%20bother%3F%20The%20answer%20is%20that%20most%20analysts%20and%20political%20observers%20in%20Turkey%20believe%20Erdogan%20will%20run%20and%20change%20the%20constitution%20to%20make%20himself%20eligible.%20He%20knows%20that%20the%20only%20person%20who%20can%20defeat%20him%20at%20the%20ballot%20is%20Imamoglu.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIstanbul%20Matters%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImamoglu%20is%20politically%20astute%2C%20can%20be%20as%20populist%20as%20Erdogan%2C%20and%20has%20proven%20his%20electoral%20strength%20by%20defeating%20Erdogan's%20candidates%20three%20times%20in%20the%20mayoral%20election%20in%20Istanbul%2C%20the%20country's%20biggest%20city%20and%20its%20economic%20engine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20loss%20of%20Istanbul%20to%20Imamoglu%20in%202019%20was%20particularly%20humiliating%20for%20the%20Turkish%20president.%20The%20election%20was%20annulled%20and%20a%20fresh%20vote%20was%20ordered%2C%20but%2C%20as%20if%20to%20rub%20salt%20into%20the%20president's%20wounds%2C%20Imamoglu%20was%20re-elected%20with%20an%20even%20bigger%20margin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EImamoglu's%20victory%20in%20the%20Istanbul%20mayoral%20election%20for%20the%20third%20time%20in%202024%20cemented%20his%20position%20as%20a%20formidable%20politician%20and%20brought%20him%20closer%20to%20challenging%20Erdogan's%20grip%20on%20Turkey's%20top%20office.%3Cbr%3E%5CnTraditionally%2C%20whoever%20controls%20Istanbul%20also%20controls%20Turkey.%20Erdogan%20himself%20started%20his%20political%20career%20in%20the%20city%20and%20rose%20to%20the%20office%20of%20mayor%20before%20becoming%20the%20national%20leader.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20also%20the%20reason%20behind%20mass%20protests.%20Most%20demonstrators%20belong%20to%20Generation%20Z%2C%20who%20have%20grown%20up%20to%20see%20only%20Erdogan%20as%20the%20national%20leader.%20They%20now%20see%20an%20alternative%20to%20him.%20Youngsters%20and%20others%20are%20turning%20out%20in%20large%20numbers%20because%20their%20demonstration%20is%20no%20longer%20limited%20to%20registering%20their%20protest%20against%20Imamoglu's%20arrest%2C%20but%20is%20also%20for%20saving%20Turkey's%20democracy%20itself.%20They%20want%20to%20see%20an%20end%20to%20Erdogan's%20increasingly%20autocratic%20rule%2C%20during%20which%20he%20has%20acquired%20vast%20influence%20over%20the%20country's%20judiciary%2C%20police%20and%20military.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20he%20has%20done%20in%20the%20past%2C%20Erdogan%20is%20using%20all%20the%20power%20at%20his%20disposal%20to%20try%20to%20suppress%20the%20protests.%20Train%20stations%20have%20been%20closed%2C%20Istanbul's%20iconic%20Taksim%20Square%20has%20been%20cordoned%20off%2C%20vehicles%20trying%20to%20reach%20protest%20sites%20are%20being%20stopped%2C%20and%20nearly%202%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20arrested%2C%20including%20a%20dozen%20journalists%20and%20lawyers.%20Imamoglu's%20advocate%2C%20Mehmet%20Pehlivan%2C%20and%20the%20CHP's%20youth%20face%2C%20the%2021-year-old%20Berkay%20Gezgin%2C%20are%20among%20those%20arrested.%20A%20Swedish%20journalist%20has%20been%20sent%20to%20jail%20and%20%3Cem%3EBBC%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecorrespondent%20Mark%20Lowen%20has%20been%20expelled.%20Notably%2C%20photographers%20have%20been%20specifically%20targeted%20to%20prevent%20the%20spread%20of%20the%20images%20of%20protests%20within%20the%20country%20and%20abroad.%20Turkey's%20Nobel%20laureate%2C%20Orhan%20Pamuk%2C%20who%20has%20been%20a%20resident%20of%20Istanbul%20for%2050%20years%2C%20has%20said%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20have%20not%20seen%20as%20many%20so-called%20security%20measures%20on%20the%20streets%20as%20I%20have%20over%20the%20past%20few%20days.%E2%80%9D%3Cbr%3E%5CnErdogan's%20crackdown%2C%20however%2C%20hasn't%20worked%20so%20far.%20The%20number%20of%20protesters%20has%20only%20increased%20in%20the%20past%20week%2C%20as%20the%20large%20demonstration%20on%20Saturday%20showed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20History%20Repeating%20Itself%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistory%20seems%20to%20be%20repeating%20itself.%20In%201998%2C%20while%20still%20mayor%20of%20Istanbul%2C%20Erdogan%20was%20arrested%20on%20charges%20of%20inciting%20racial%20hatred%20and%20spent%20four%20months%20in%20jail.%20His%20arrest%20only%20made%20him%20more%20popular%20and%20brought%20him%20to%20the%20national%20stage.%20That%20helped%20him%20later%20become%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20then%20the%20President%20of%20Turkey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDoes%20a%20similar%20fate%20await%20Imamoglu%3F%20No%20one%20can%20say%20for%20sure.%20But%20the%20Erdogan%20regime's%20move%20against%20him%20does%20indicate%20that%20the%20imprisoned%20Istanbul%20mayor%20is%20seen%20as%20the%20biggest%20political%20threat%20to%20the%20President.%20Days%20after%20Imamoglu's%20arrest%20on%20March%2019%2C%20his%20CHP%20party%20organised%20a%20vote%20to%20nominate%20him%20for%20the%20presidency.%20Nearly%2015%20million%20people%20turned%20up%20nationwide%20to%20vote%20for%20him.%20The%20number%20was%20several%20times%20bigger%20than%20his%20party's%20total%20membership%20of%20under%20two%20million.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBoth%20Erdogan%20and%20Imamoglu%20come%20from%20the%20Black%20Sea%20region%20of%20Turkey%20and%20moved%20to%20Istanbul%20with%20their%20parents%20and%20grew%20up%20in%20the%20city.%20While%20Imamoglu%20has%20been%20more%20popular%20among%20secularists%2C%20Erdogan%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20hero%20in%20the%20Anatolia%20region%2C%20the%20Asian%20part%20of%20Turkey%2C%20and%20rural%20areas.%20He%20has%20used%20political%20Islam%20to%20expand%20his%20base.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20reason%20Erdogan%20was%20arrested%20and%20imprisoned%20in%201998%20was%20because%20he%20challenged%20the%20strict%20secular%20principles%20of%20the%20modern%20Turkish%20state%2C%20founded%20by%20Mustafa%20Kemal%20Ataturk%2C%20by%20reciting%20a%20poem%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20mosques%20are%20our%20barracks%2C%20the%20domes%20our%20helmets%2C%20the%20minarets%20our%20bayonets%20and%20the%20faithful%20our%20soldiers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20party%20was%20banned%2C%20but%20Erdogan%20formed%20a%20new%20political%20group%20after%20his%20release.%20Once%20in%20power%2C%20he%20expanded%20his%20Islamist%20base.%20First%20as%20Prime%20Minister%20from%202003%20and%20then%20as%20directly%20elected%20president%20since%202014%2C%20Erdogan%20has%20tried%20to%20portray%20himself%20as%20a%20democratic%20Islamist.%20He%20did%20remove%20the%20ban%20on%20wearing%20headscarves.%20However%2C%20he%20has%20also%20asked%20the%20Turkish%20people%20to%20have%20more%20children.%20As%20a%20father%20of%20four%2C%20he%20declared%20that%20%26quot%3Bno%20Muslim%20family%26quot%3B%20should%20consider%20birth%20control%20or%20family%20planning.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20multiply%20our%20descendants%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20May%202016.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20he%20appealed%20to%20Turkish%20people%20living%20in%20Europe%20to%20have%20at%20least%20five%20children.%20He%20also%20doesn't%20believe%20in%20equal%20rights%20for%20men%20and%20women.%20Many%20Turks%20are%20not%20comfortable%20with%20such%20views%20and%20Erdogan's%20political%20Islam%20policy%20as%20they%20still%20believe%20in%20the%20secular%20principles%20of%20Ataturk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EControl%20Of%20the%20Judiciary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EErdogan%20had%20used%20the%20failed%202016%20military%20coup%20to%20launch%20a%20massive%20clampdown%20against%20his%20critics.%20He%20accused%20them%20of%20being%20associated%20with%20the%20Gulen%20movement%2C%20inspired%20by%20the%20teachings%20of%20late%20Turkish%20Muslim%20scholar%20Fethullah%20Gulen%2C%20whom%20he%20accused%20of%20being%20behind%20the%20coup%20attempt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20sacked%201%2C50%2C000%20people%20from%20government%20posts%20and%20arrested%2050%2C000%2C%20including%20journalists%2C%20lawyers%2C%20students%20and%20other%20critics.%20But%20the%20most%20worrying%20action%20for%20Turks%20was%20the%20purge%20in%20the%20judiciary.%20More%20than%204%2C300%20judges%20were%20removed%20and%201%2C100%20arrested%20and%20replaced%20by%20Erdogan%20loyalists%20and%20inexperienced%20newcomers.%20About%201%2C600%20lawyers%20were%20prosecuted%20and%20nearly%20500%20were%20given%20long%20prison%20sentences.%20The%20way%20judges%20are%20appointed%20was%20also%20changed%20after%20the%202017%20constitution%20amendment.%20The%20president%20now%20appoints%20four%20members%20of%20the%20committee%20that%20hire%20and%20fire%20judges.%20Seven%20members%20are%20appointed%20by%20parliament%2C%20where%20Erdogan%20has%20a%20majority%2C%20and%20the%20remaining%20two%20are%20the%20Justice%20Minister%20and%20one%20of%20his%20deputies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ECan%20Imamoglu%20Get%20a%20Fair%20Trial%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20reasons%20given%20above%2C%20Imamoglu's%20supporters%20are%20unsure%20whether%20he%20can%20get%20a%20fair%20trial.%20In%20his%20statements%20since%20the%20arrest%2C%20he%20has%20avoided%20criticising%20the%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20independent%20observers%20believe%20the%20charges%20against%20him%20will%20not%20stick%20in%20a%20fair%20trial.%20But%20will%20Turkey's%20judges%20act%20impartially%20and%20provide%20justice%20to%20Imamoglu%3F%20Or%20will%20they%20go%20along%20with%20the%20wishes%20of%20Erdogan%2C%20who%20would%20like%20his%20opponent%20to%20be%20disqualified%20from%20running%20for%20the%20presidency%3F%20There%20is%20hardly%20any%20international%20pressure%20on%20the%20Turkish%20President%20in%20the%20current%20geopolitical%20environment.%20US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20is%20known%20to%20be%20a%20fan.%20Turkey%20is%20a%20member%20of%20NATO%2C%20and%20the%20European%20Union%20needs%20Erdogan%20because%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20conflict.%20He%20also%20has%20good%20relations%20with%20the%20Russian%20leader%2C%20Vladimir%20Putin.%20The%20other%20big%20power%2C%20China%2C%20is%20not%20known%20for%20speaking%20out%20against%20repression.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20only%20domestic%20pressure%20can%20make%20any%20difference.%20The%20future%20of%20Turkey's%20democracy%20appears%20to%20rest%20on%20young%20protesters'%20shoulders.%20Twelve%20years%20ago%2C%20during%20the%20Gezi%20Park%20mass%20protests%2C%20when%20they%20thought%20they%20were%20about%20to%20make%20history%2C%20the%20Erdogan%20government%20brutally%20crushed%20the%20uprising.%20This%20time%2C%20they%20are%20backed%20by%20the%20country's%20main%20opposition%20party%2C%20which%20controls%20six%20out%20of%20the%20seven%20biggest%20cities%20of%20Turkey.%20In%20Imamoglu%2C%20they%20have%20also%20found%20a%20charismatic%20leader.%20But%20Erdogan%20controls%20the%20parliament%2C%20judiciary%2C%20army%2C%20police%20and%20most%20of%20the%20Turkish%20media.%20No%20one%20can%20predict%20what%20he%20will%20do%20next.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Naresh%20Kaushik%20is%20a%20former%20editor%20at%20the%20Associated%20Press%20and%20BBC%20News%20and%20is%20based%20in%20London)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743425940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2015-09%2Fturkeys-president-tayyip-erdogan_650x400_61443526086.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fturkey-history-comes-back-to-bite-erdogan-8054385%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%201998%2C%20while%20still%20mayor%20of%20Istanbul%2C%20Erdogan%20was%20arrested%20on%20charges%20of%20inciting%20racial%20hatred%20and%20spent%20four%20months%20in%20jail.%20His%20arrest%20only%20made%20him%20more%20popular%20and%20brought%20him%20to%20the%20national%20stage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fturkey-history-comes-back-to-bite-erdogan-8054385%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Malaika-Sangakkara%20spark%20DATING%20rumours%3B%20Here%E2%80%99s%20the%20truth!%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743425855000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toi