Ms%20Tewari%2C%20who%20could%20be%20one%20of%20the%20youngest%20officers%20in%20the%20post%2C%20is%20from%20Mehmurganj%20in%20Varanasi%2C%20the%20constituency%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20represents%20in%20parliament%20since%202014.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBefore%20clearing%20the%20Civil%20Services%20Examination%2C%20Ms%20Tewari%20worked%20as%20the%20Assistant%20Commissioner%20(Commercial%20Tax)%20in%20Varanasi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETelevision%20news%20channel%20News18%20reported%20that%20she%20secured%2096th%20rank%20in%20the%20exam%20conducted%20by%20the%20Union%20Public%20Services%20Commission.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnBefore%20joining%20the%20PMO%2C%20she%20worked%20in%20the%20foreign%20ministry's%20Disarmament%20and%20International%20Security%20Affairs%20Division.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20she%20joined%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20Office%20as%20Under%20Secretary%20and%20was%20promoted%20to%20the%20post%20of%20the%20Deputy%20Secretary%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20Office%2C%20she%20served%20in%20the%20'Foreign%20and%20Security'%20section%20and%20took%20care%20of%20areas%20including%20foreign%20affairs%2C%20security%20and%20atomic%20energy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20expertise%20in%20international%20relations%20helped%20her%20play%20a%20key%20role%20and%20she%20reported%20directly%20to%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20Ajit%20Doval.%20Her%20in-depth%20knowledge%20was%20proved%20crucial%20during%20India's%20presidency%20of%20G20.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743421980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fdr31sdtc_nidhi-tewari_625x300_31_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnidhi-tewari-ifs-officer-from-pm-narendra-modis-constituency-his-new-private-secretary-8053979%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nidhi%20Tewari%2C%20a%202014-batch%20officer%20of%20the%20Indian%20Foreign%20Service%2C%20will%20take%20over%20as%20the%20next%20private%20secretary%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20She%20is%20currently%20serving%20as%20the%20Deputy%20Secretary%20in%20the%20Prime%20Minister's%20Office%20or%20PMO%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fnidhi-tewari-ifs-officer-from-pm-narendra-modis-constituency-his-new-private-secretary-8053979%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Tired%20Of%20Waiting%2C%20UP%20Villagers%20Building%20108-Ft%20Bridge%20With%20Crowdfunding%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThey%20waited%2C%20waited%2C%20waited%20and%20then%20decided%20not%20to%20wait%20anymore.%20A%20group%20of%20villagers%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh's%20Ghazipur%20district%2C%20tired%20of%20waiting%20for%20local%20representatives%20to%20fulfill%20their%20promises%20to%20get%20a%20bridge%20built%2C%20have%20taken%20matters%20into%20their%20own%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20108-ft%20bridge%2C%20paid%20for%20by%20the%20villagers%2C%20is%20now%20coming%20up%20on%20the%20Magai%20river.%20The%20villagers%20have%20been%20pooling%20money%20to%20arrange%20the%20required%20funds%20of%20nearly%20Rs%201%20crore.%20They%20said%20they%20have%20repeatedly%20raised%20their%20demand%20for%20the%20bridge%2C%20but%20have%20only%20received%20promises.%20The%20foundation%20stone%20for%20the%20bridge%20was%20laid%20in%20February%20last%20year%20and%20work%20is%20now%20in%20full%20swing.%20Administrative%20questions%2C%20however%2C%20remain.%20The%20bridge%20is%20being%20constructed%20without%20the%20administration's%20permission%20and%20in%20that%20case%2C%20a%20big%20question%20is%20how%20accountability%20would%20be%20fixed%20if%20there%20is%20an%20accident%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20resident%20Rajesh%20Singh%20Yadav%2C%20who%20has%20worked%20with%20the%20village%20headman%2C%20said%20the%20bridge's%20construction%20is%20halfway%20done.%20%26quot%3BFrom%20Independence%20to%20now%2C%20every%20elected%20representative%20has%20only%20cheated%20the%20people.%20That's%20why%20this%20bridge%20was%20not%20built.%20People%20vote%20and%20realise%20later%20that%20the%20representative%20is%20doing%20nothing%20for%20them.%20People%20from%20at%20least%2050%20villages%20will%20benefit%20from%20this%20bridge.%20If%20this%20bridge%20is%20built%2C%20the%20distance%20to%20the%20district%20headquarters%20will%20be%20reduced%20by%2025%20km%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnil%20Yadav%2C%20another%20resident%2C%20said%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20bridge%20has%20hit%20the%20villagers'%20education.%20He%20said%20there%20is%20no%20degree%20college%20in%20the%20area%20and%20one%20must%20move%20to%20Ghazipur%20for%20higher%20education%20because%20the%20travel%20time%20is%20too%20long.%20%26quot%3BIf%20we%20stay%20there%2C%20we%20have%20to%20rent%20a%20room.%20We%20are%20farmers%2C%20where%20is%20the%20money%3F%20Students%20get%20late%20for%20school%20when%20the%20river%20is%20flooded.%20They%20have%20to%20wait%20for%20boats%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Asked%20when%20they%20expect%20the%20bridge%20to%20be%20completed%2C%20he%20replied%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20cannot%20say%20for%20sure.%20Because%20work%20depends%20on%20the%20money%20we%20can%20collect.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocal%20residents%20said%20a%20former%20Armyman%20from%20the%20area%20led%20the%20initiative%20to%20build%20the%20bridge.%20Ravindra%20Yadav%2C%20who%20retired%20from%20the%20Army's%20Corps%20of%20Engineers%2C%20donated%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20for%20the%20bridge%20construction.%20%26quot%3BHe%20donated%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%20The%20foundation%20stone%20was%20laid%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20Allahabad%20High%20Court%20judge%20Shekhar%20Kumar%20Yadav.%20Gradually%2C%20a%20message%20went%20out%20to%20the%20people%2C%20and%20they%20joined%20the%20cause.%20Once%20this%20bridge%20is%20built%2C%20we%20can%20easily%20access%20hospitals%2C%20schools%20and%20colleges%20in%20Ghazipur%2C%26quot%3B%20Ramkriti%20Yadav%2C%20who%20led%20the%20panchayat%20earlier.%20He%20said%20the%20Army%20veteran%20had%20worked%20on%20such%20projects%20earlier%20and%20was%20overseeing%20the%20construction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Mohammabad%20Assembly%20constituency%2C%20currently%20represented%20by%20Samajwadi%20Party's%20Suhaib%20Ansari%2C%20has%20oscillated%20between%20two%20families%20for%20the%20past%20four%20decades%20--%20the%20Rais%20and%20the%20Ansaris.%20The%20segment%20has%20also%20seen%20a%20bloody%20political%20history.%20From%201985%20to%202001%2C%20the%20seat%20was%20represented%20by%20Afzal%20Ansari%2C%20the%20brother%20of%20gangster-politician%20Mukhtar%20Ansari.%20In%20the%202002%20polls%2C%20BJP's%20Krishnanand%20Rai%20was%20elected%20MLA%20from%20the%20Ansari%20stronghold.%20Four%20years%20later%2C%20Rai%20was%20murdered%20on%20the%20orders%20of%20Mukhtar%20Ansari.%20In%20the%20election%20that%20followed%2C%20his%20wife%2C%20Alka%20Rai%2C%20was%20elected%20MLA.%20Alka%20Rai%20won%20the%20seat%20in%202017%20too%2C%20but%20lost%20it%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20the%20ancestral%20village%20of%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20Lieutenant%20Governor%20and%20BJP%20veteran%20Manoj%20Sinha%20is%20also%20located%20in%20this%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDistrict%20collector%20Aryaka%20Akhauri%20said%20the%20administration%20came%20to%20know%20about%20the%20bridge%20from%20media%20reports.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20a%20matter%20of%20public%20safety%20and%20heavy%20vehicles%20will%20use%20it.%20So%20we%20will%20get%20it%20checked%20to%20ensure%20the%20quality%20of%20construction%20so%20that%20no%20accident%20takes%20place%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EInputs%20by%20Sunil%20Singh%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743420780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fn0jnqqk_up-bridge_625x300_31_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftired-of-waiting-up-villagers-building-108-ft-bridge-with-crowdfunding-8053842%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22They%20waited%2C%20waited%2C%20waited%20and%20then%20decided%20not%20to%20wait%20anymore.%20A%20group%20of%20villagers%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh's%20Ghazipur%20district%2C%20tired%20of%20waiting%20for%20local%20representatives%20to%20fulfill%20promises%20to%20get%20a%20bridge%20built%2C%20have%20taken%20matters%20into%20their%20hands%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Ftired-of-waiting-up-villagers-building-108-ft-bridge-with-crowdfunding-8053842%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Nalco%20draws%20Parl%20panel%20flak%20for%20spending%20under%2050%25%20of%20targeted%20capex%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743420770000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fnalco-draws-parl-panel-flak-for-spending-under-50-of-targeted-capex-125033100579_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Against%20the%20targeted%20capex%20of%20Rs%202%2C000%20crore%20by%20Nalco%20for%20the%20year%202024-25%2C%20the%20end%20of%20January%202025%2C%20the%20capex%20stood%20at%20Rs%20879%20crore%2C%20that%20is%20less%20than%2050%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20targeted%20amount%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fnalco-draws-parl-panel-flak-for-spending-under-50-of-targeted-capex-125033100579_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Indian%20Drugs%2C%20Pak%20Terrorism%2C%20China%3A%20Inside%20The%20Latest%20US%20Intel%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20release%20of%20the%20first%20combined%20intelligence%20assessment%20of%20the%20United%20States%20is%20no%20small%20thing%2C%20given%20that%20there%20is%20a%20new%20administration%20under%20an%20ebullient%20President%2C%20Donald%20Trump.%20Add%20to%20that%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20comes%20under%20the%20leadership%20of%20Tulsi%20Gabbard%2C%20only%20the%20second%20woman%20to%20be%20the%20Director%20of%20National%20Intelligence.%20And%20no%2C%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20anything%20at%20all%20that%20she's%20a%20practising%20Hindu.%20That's%20not%20how%20it%20works.%20This%20is%20the%20combined%20report%20of%2018%20intelligence%20agencies%2C%20and%20that's%20what%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Intel%20On%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%20off%2C%20the%20issues%20flagged%20about%20India.%20The%20media%20called%20Gabbard%20out%20for%20linking%20India%20to%20the%20serious%20problem%20of%20fentanyl%2C%20a%20synthetic%20opioid%20that%2C%20while%20legitimately%20used%20to%20treat%20severe%20pain%2C%20has%20become%20the%20leading%20drug%20crisis%20in%20the%20US%2C%20which%20President%20Trump%20is%20taking%20very%20seriously%20and%20using%20for%20all%20manner%20of%20things%2C%20including%20sanctions.%20In%20her%20Congressional%20statement%2C%20Gabbard%20did%20refer%20to%20India%20and%20China%20as%20sources%20for%20%E2%80%98dual%20use'%20chemicals%20that%20feed%20the%20drug%20trade.%20But%20this%20is%20an%20old%20issue%20that%20has%20seen%20Delhi%20cooperating%20with%20US%20agencies%20in%20dealing%20with%20groups%20that%20had%20shifted%20from%20China%20to%20India%2C%20at%20least%20since%202018%2C%20as%20Beijing%20cracked%20down%20on%20the%20trade%20that%20supplied%20Mexican%20cartels.%20India%20has%20since%20banned%20these%20precursors%2C%20and%20a%20number%20of%20Chinese%20were%20arrested%20too.%20But%20clearly%2C%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done.%20Just%20recently%2C%20a%20Hyderabad%20firm%20in%20an%20upscale%20neighbourhood%20was%20indicted%20for%20openly%20selling%20precursors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECracking%20down%20on%20this%20is%20vital%2C%20since%20India%20already%20has%20a%20serious%20drug%20problem%20that%20constitutes%20a%20public%20health%20crisis.%20Back%20to%20the%20DNI%20report%2C%20which%20under%20the%20Biden%20administration%20had%20a%20lot%20more%20to%20say%20on%20India%2C%20including%20references%20to%20%E2%80%98alleged'%20Pakistan%20support%20to%20terrorism%20and%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi's%20willingness%20to%20use%20force%20against%20%E2%80%9Cperceived%20or%20real%20Pakistani%20provocations%E2%80%9D.%20Certainly%2C%20the%20present%20assessment%20is%20far%20better%20for%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPakistan%20Gets%20A%20Break%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20that%20Pakistan%20didn't%20get%20what%20it%20wanted.%20Clearly%2C%20the%20arrest%2C%20apparently%20with%20the%20support%20of%20Pakistani%20authorities%2C%20of%20the%20alleged%20%E2%80%98mastermind'%20of%20the%202021%20Abbey%20Gate%20bombing%20in%20Kabul%20that%20had%20killed%2013%20Americans%2C%20was%20a%20nice%20play%20by%20Rawalpindi.%20That%20Mohammed%20Sharifullah%2C%20aka%20'Jafar'%2C%20was%20arrested%20quite%20conveniently%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98Pakistan-Afghanistan'%20border%E2%80%94with%20the%20onus%20being%20placed%20on%20Afghanistan%E2%80%94demonstrates%20Pakistan's%20proven%20habit%20of%20pulling%20terrorists%20out%20of%20a%20hat%20whenever%20a%20suitable%20occasion%20presents%20itself.%20That%20has%20been%20done%20earlier%20too%2C%20what%20with%20repatriating%20Chechens%20to%20Russia%20and%20Uyghurs%20to%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20US%20intelligence%20officers%20are%20hardly%20novices%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20Pakistan.%20Islamabad's%20intel%20has%20been%20waging%20a%20long%20campaign%2C%20including%20in%20US%20academic%20institutions%2C%20to%20link%20the%20Tehrik-e-Taliban%20Pakistan%20(TTP)%20to%20al%20Qaeda%20and%20the%20Islamic%20State%E2%80%94in%20UN%20documents%20too%E2%80%94and%20project%20it%20as%20an%20%E2%80%98international%20threat'.%20In%20a%20part%20win%2C%20the%20DNI's%20latest%20assessment%20names%20the%20group%20as%20a%20%E2%80%98potential%20future%20threat'%2C%20and%20does%20not%20mention%20Pakistan%20beyond%20that.%20That's%20a%20relief%20for%20an%20embattled%20Pakistan%20army%2C%20but%20not%20quite%20enough.%20Expect%20more%20TTP%20attacks%20in%20the%20subcontinent%20that%20tie%20it%20up%20firmly%20to%20al%20Qaeda%20or%20the%20Islamic%20State.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20The%20Chinese%20Wind%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20issue%20of%20non-state%20actors%20of%20all%20kinds%20takes%20precedence%20in%20the%20report%2C%20the%20section%20on%20China%20is%20far%20more%20hard-hitting%20than%20the%20earlier%20reports.%20Where%20the%202024%20document%20had%20outlined%20China's%20various%20weaknesses%2C%20the%20present%20report%20states%20boldly%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20PLA%20has%20the%20capability%20to%20conduct%20long-range%20precision%20strikes%20with%20conventional%20weapons%20against%20the%20Homeland's%20periphery%20in%20the%20Western%20Pacific%2C%20including%20Guam%2C%20Hawaii%2C%20and%20Alaska%E2%80%9D.%20It%20also%20adds%20realistically%20that%20the%20US%20should%20not%20be%20involved%20in%20a%20Taiwan%20conflict%2C%20as%20such%20an%20event%20would%20result%20in%20%E2%80%9Cdisrupt%5Bing%5D%20U.S.%20access%20to%20trade%20and%20semiconductor%20technology%20critical%20to%20the%20global%20economy%E2%80%A6significant%20and%20costly%20consequences%20to%20US%20and%20global%20economic%20and%20security%20interests%E2%80%9D.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20this%20is%20a%20pitch%20for%20the%20militarisation%20of%20Greenland%20and%20for%20a%20strengthening%20of%20the%20Indo-Pacific%2C%20though%20it%20says%20nothing%20about%20the%20Quad.%20Those%20conclusions%20are%20to%20be%20drawn%20by%20policymakers%2C%20not%20intel%20providers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERussia%20Is%20Still%20A%20Threat.%20So%20Is%20Hamas%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Russia%2C%20the%20intelligence%20argument%20that%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war%20has%20pushed%20Moscow%20towards%20Beijing%2C%20forming%20a%20direct%20threat%20to%20the%20US%2C%20is%20the%20most%20significant%20conclusion%20that%20will%20be%20welcomed%20by%20most%20Asian%20states%20that%20have%20some%20strategic%20sense.%20This%20argument%20was%20never%20accepted%20by%20the%20earlier%20administration.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20document%20is%20far%20from%20writing%20off%20the%20Russian%20threat.%20It%20notes%20that%20despite%20the%20long%20war%2C%20Moscow%20has%20shown%20unexpected%20resilience%20and%20continues%20to%20remain%20a%20strategic%20threat%20to%20the%20US%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20not%20just%20its%20nuclear%20capabilities%20but%20strong%20disinformation%20capabilities%20too%2C%20designed%20to%20divide%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%20there's%20the%20view%20on%20Iran%2C%20which%20notes%20its%20degraded%20capabilities%20with%20regard%20to%20Hamas%20and%20others%2C%20as%20well%20as%20its%20regional%20environment.%20Overall%2C%20the%20intelligence%20line%20is%20much%20softer%20on%20the%20Teeran%20threat%2C%20which%20was%20hyped%20by%20the%20earlier%20administration.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Trump's%20offer%20of%20a%20new%20nuclear%20deal%20has%20been%20accepted%20by%20Iran.%20This%20will%20go%20via%20Oman%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20UAE%2C%20which%20had%20been%20the%20first%20line%20of%20approach%20for%20Washington.%20Trump's%20threat%20that%20%E2%80%9Cbad%2C%20bad%20things%E2%80%9D%20will%20happen%20to%20Iran%20is%20backed%20by%20the%20airstrikes%20against%20the%20Houthis%2C%20another%20Tehran%20prop.%20There's%20no%20mistaking%20that%20message.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnIntel%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20is%20far%20from%20writing%20off%20Hamas.%20They%20expect%20the%20region%20to%20remain%20%E2%80%98volatile'.%20Translate%20that%20into%20the%20finding%20that%20Washington's%20backing%20of%20Israel%20in%20clearing%20out%20Gaza%20will%20continue%2C%20even%20as%20Arab%20states%20squabble%20among%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20Violent%20World%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%2C%20the%20DNI%20report%20points%20to%20the%20expectation%20of%20a%20more%20violent%20world%2C%20where%20the%20threat%20arises%20from%20cooperation%20between%20%E2%80%98adversaries'%20like%20Russia%2C%20China%2C%20Iran%20and%20North%20Korea%2C%20and%20possibly%20others.%20That%20was%20not%20ever%20foreseen%20in%20the%202024%20report%2C%20though%20all%20the%20markers%20indicating%20it%20were%20there.%20Intel%20was%2C%20after%20all%2C%20well%20aware%20of%20Chinese%20assistance%20to%20Russia%2C%20and%20the%20relationship%20between%20Iran%2C%20China%20and%20Russia.%20For%20India%2C%20as%20with%20much%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20Global%20South%2C%20this%20focus%20on%20%E2%80%98adversarial%20cooperation'%20puts%20many%20countries%20at%20the%20risk%20of%20being%20seen%20as%20close%20to%20one%20or%20the%20other.%20But%20so%20far%20as%20is%20evident%2C%20the%20thrust%20of%20Trump's%20policy%20is%20to%20splice%20Russia%20away%20from%20China%20as%20rapidly%20as%20possible%2C%20even%20while%20holding%20out%20a%20branch%E2%80%94although%20a%20very%20sharp%20one%E2%80%94to%20Iran.%20That%20will%20leave%20China%20isolated%2C%20only%20with%20its%20%E2%80%98all-weather%20friend'%20Pakistan.%20That%20last%20link%20may%20change%20too%2C%20as%20Rawalpindi%20is%20eager%20to%20get%20US%20drones%20on%20the%20ground%2C%20if%20not%20boots.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20it%20is%20vital%20that%20India%20gets%20its%20stringent%20counter-drug%20policies%20effective%20on%20the%20ground%20so%20that%20a%20range%20of%20dangerous%20chemicals%20are%20actually%20stopped%20rather%20than%20being%20quietly%20sold%20to%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20government%20might%20also%20want%20to%20make%20its%20own%20intelligence%20assessment%2C%20which%20will%20probably%20be%20the%20most%20unenviable%20task%20of%20the%20year.%20The%20global%20situation%20is%20a%20shifting%2C%20murky%20river.%20Nothing%20at%20all%20is%20certain.%20A%20little%20more%20in%20terms%20of%20resources%20for%20intel%20wouldn't%20hurt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Tara%20Kartha%20is%20a%20former%20director%20of%20the%20National%20Security%20Council%20Secretariat)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743420600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2Fio1465uo_intel_625x300_31_March_25.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findian-drugs-pak-terrorism-china-decoding-the-latest-us-intel-report-8053793%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20latest%20DNI%20report%20points%20to%20the%20expectation%20of%20a%20more%20violent%20world%2C%20where%20the%20threat%20arises%20from%20cooperation%20between%20'adversaries'%20like%20Russia%2C%20China%2C%20Iran%20and%20North%20Korea%2C%20and%20possibly%20others.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Findian-drugs-pak-terrorism-china-decoding-the-latest-us-intel-report-8053793%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump%20agrees%20to%20meet%20Bill%20Maher%20at%20White%20House%20after%20request%20from%20Kid%20Rock%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743420600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119798928%2Cimgsize-702583.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fdonald-trump-agrees-to-meet-bill-maher-at-white-house-after-request-from-kid-rock%2Farticleshow%2F119797862.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F119797862.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EUS%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20agreed%20to%20meet%20comedian%20Bill%20Maher%20at%20the%20White%20House%20after%20a%20request%20from%20Kid%20Rock.%20Despite%20Trump's%20reservations%2C%20he%20found%20the%20idea%20interesting%20and